DAMATURU- Satisfied with the performance of Senator Ibrahim Mohammed Bomai representing Yobe South senatorial district of Yobe state, constituent groups have today met at the multi-purpose hall of the Federal College of Education (Technical) Potiskum to raise funds as well drum their support for his re-election in 2023. The groups collectively donated the over N45 million naira to the senator and said that they’re immediately proceeding to Abuja after the sallah to obtain the nomination form. The donors comprise of Yobe South Movement for Good Governance, National Association of Automobile Technicians (NATA), Ma’ina Kara, Mbeno Association, Students Union and National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW). In his welcome address, the Zonal Coordinator Senator Bomai Movement, Muhammad Buhari Yusuf revealed that the senator has delivered democracy dividends to the electorates of the zone. Barrister Khalil Halilu enumerated some of the achievements of the senator within the period under review. On his part, the Chairman of APC Potiskum Local Government Area, Bala Musa Lawan said that they are satisfied with the achievements of the senator “he’s a good leader with all the qualities of leadership, we are calling on him to re-contest in 2023 elections”. Abubakar Baba Dada described the performance of the senator Bomai as beyond words “we will keep on mobilizing people to vote for him in order to continue executing numerous projects. Yusuf Zaki, PRO of Ma’ina Kara Association stated that their association alone donated the sum of N5 million naira as part of their support. POLL The Councillor representing Dogo Nini ward of Potiskum Local Government Council, Musa Dahiru Abdullahi threw encomiums to the Senator for the achievements recorded while Ibrahim Mohammed, Secretary Bomai Support Group said that they have not regretted voting the senator.